column2: Did you go on any rides this week?

column32: Biked around plano! Felt great, except my neck hurt.

column27: We rode from my brother's house, to the base, to the Art Museum and back. I couldn't tell if it was my knees or legs just being tense that was bothering me, so that is something to keep an eye on.

column7: Soooo Raveena and I thought we could ride around inner city Houston and it was a bad idea. We rode on Westheimer (worst idea ever, Ozarks route should not go on this street) I ride on this street and had never realized how awful it was for cyclists. So we biked around my neighborhood and then I awkwardly got us lost.
column32: Ellen and I rode with the Northwest Cycling Club. It was super awesome and was great since a woman knew the route since she had done it every week for almost 2 years and everyone in our ride group was really accepting and understanding that she and I were new riders. We also got some donations and free breakfast! woohoo.

column7: Rode in The Woodlands. Pretty good communication, one flat and one person fell.

column32: Rode with a Houston ride group. Off 290 with a group of cyclists

column7: The ride went well, we were on a route in the Woodlands.

column22:
Scenic Loop ride in San Antonio:

Bandera > Scenic Loop > Boerne Stage Rd > I-10 > 1604 > Bandera

column7: Shoal creek loop over and over.
column22: Shoal creek then some hill training in Northwest Hills area. Hills were tough but as a rider it's important to get lots of exposure to them!

column7: Wonderful ride! Please excuse my brevity -- filling this form out on my phone while sitting in a hotel room. :)
column22: Great ride! Again, please excuse my brevity -- filling this form out on my phone while sitting in a hotel room. :)

column32:
North Plano/Dallas area. Was 75% road-based/no trails. Good ride, I feel more comfortable biking on road now. Had one issue regarding left turn lanes- we accidentally got in the far left one/ was kind of difficult getting back over. Otherwise no problems. Akos got a GPS on his phone and it worked really well

My odometer is still not cooperating so used Akos' stats

column7:
It was a good ride. A lot was learned
Dani go a flat and she was prepared to fix it.
Hali feel but it was the most graceful thing ever.
Wind sucks.
Rode around the woodlands. The terrain had nice inclines so it was good hill riding practice. Good scenery. Was challenging but all in all a great ride.

We rode in Houston, which is never the best idea... Unfortunately we were stranded in a part of Houston where we literally couldn't cross the road and had to call Becca's dad to pick us up. After that we stayed on the safe side and rode only around the River Oaks neighborhood. Literally in circles.
